methods.name: getDeclaringClass
methods.description: Returns the class in which the cracked method handle's underlying member was defined.

methods.name: getMethodType
methods.description: Returns the nominal type of the cracked symbolic reference, expressed as a method type.

methods.name: getModifiers
methods.description: Returns the access modifiers of the underlying member.

methods.name: getName
methods.description: Returns the name of the cracked method handle's underlying member.

methods.name: getReferenceKind
methods.description: Returns the reference kind of the cracked method handle, which in turn determines whether the method handle's underlying member was a constructor, method, or field.

methods.name: isVarArgs
methods.description: Determines if the underlying member was a variable arity method or constructor.

methods.name: referenceKindToString
methods.description: Returns the descriptive name of the given reference kind, as defined in the table above.

methods.name: reflectAs
methods.description: Reflects the underlying member as a method, constructor, or field object.

methods.name: toString
methods.description: Returns a string representation for a MethodHandleInfo, given the four parts of its symbolic reference.

methods.name: asCollector
methods.description: Makes an array-collecting method handle, which accepts a given number of positional arguments starting at a given position, and collects them into an array argument.

methods.name: asCollector
methods.description: Makes an array-collecting method handle, which accepts a given number of trailing positional arguments and collects them into an array argument.

methods.name: asFixedArity
methods.description: Makes a fixed arity method handle which is otherwise equivalent to the current method handle.

methods.name: asSpreader
methods.description: Makes an array-spreading method handle, which accepts an array argument at a given position and spreads its elements as positional arguments in place of the array.

methods.name: asSpreader
methods.description: Makes an array-spreading method handle, which accepts a trailing array argument and spreads its elements as positional arguments.

methods.name: asType
methods.description: Produces an adapter method handle which adapts the type of the current method handle to a new type.

methods.name: asVarargsCollector
methods.description: Makes a variable arity adapter which is able to accept any number of trailing positional arguments and collect them into an array argument.

methods.name: bindTo
methods.description: Binds a value x to the first argument of a method handle, without invoking it.

methods.name: describeConstable
methods.description: Return a nominal descriptor for this instance, if one can be constructed, or an empty Optional if one cannot be.

methods.name: invoke
methods.description: Invokes the method handle, allowing any caller type descriptor, and optionally performing conversions on arguments and return values.

methods.name: invokeExact
methods.description: Invokes the method handle, allowing any caller type descriptor, but requiring an exact type match.

methods.name: invokeWithArguments
methods.description: Performs a variable arity invocation, passing the arguments in the given array to the method handle, as if via an inexact invoke from a call site which mentions only the type Object, and whose actual argument count is the length of the argument array.

methods.name: invokeWithArguments
methods.description: Performs a variable arity invocation, passing the arguments in the given list to the method handle, as if via an inexact invoke from a call site which mentions only the type Object, and whose actual argument count is the length of the argument list.

methods.name: isVarargsCollector
methods.description: Determines if this method handle supports variable arity calls.

methods.name: toString
methods.description: Returns a string representation of the method handle, starting with the string "MethodHandle" and ending with the string representation of the method handle's type.

methods.name: type
methods.description: Reports the type of this method handle.

methods.name: withVarargs
methods.description: Adapts this method handle to be variable arity if the boolean flag is true, else fixed arity.

methods.name: valueOf
methods.description: Returns the enum constant of this class with the specified name.

methods.name: values
methods.description: Returns an array containing the constants of this enum class, inthe order they are declared.

methods.name: asInterfaceInstance
methods.description: Produces an instance of the given single-method interface which redirects its calls to the given method handle.

methods.name: isWrapperInstance
methods.description: Determines if the given object was produced by a call to asInterfaceInstance.

methods.name: wrapperInstanceTarget
methods.description: Produces or recovers a target method handle which is behaviorally equivalent to the unique method of this wrapper instance.

methods.name: wrapperInstanceType
methods.description: Recovers the unique single-method interface type for which this wrapper instance was created.

fields.name: MODULE

fields.name: ORIGINAL
fields.description: A single-bit mask representing original access  which may contribute to the result of lookupModes.

fields.name: PACKAGE
fields.description: A single-bit mask representing package access (default access),  which may contribute to the result of lookupModes.

fields.name: PRIVATE
fields.description: A single-bit mask representing private access,  which may contribute to the result of lookupModes.

fields.name: PROTECTED
fields.description: A single-bit mask representing protected access,  which may contribute to the result of lookupModes.

fields.name: PUBLIC
fields.description: A single-bit mask representing public access,  which may contribute to the result of lookupModes.

fields.name: UNCONDITIONAL
fields.description: A single-bit mask representing unconditional access  which may contribute to the result of lookupModes.

methods.name: accessClass

methods.name: bind
methods.description: Produces an early-bound method handle for a non-static method.

methods.name: defineClass
methods.description: Creates and links a class or interface from bytes with the same class loader and in the same runtime package and protection domain as this lookup's lookup class as if calling ClassLoader::defineClass.

methods.name: defineHiddenClass
methods.description: Creates a hidden class or interface from bytes, returning a Lookup on the newly created class or interface.

methods.name: defineHiddenClassWithClassData
methods.description: Creates a hidden class or interface from bytes with associated class data, returning a Lookup on the newly created class or interface.

methods.name: dropLookupMode

methods.name: ensureInitialized

methods.name: findClass

methods.name: findGetter

methods.name: findSetter

methods.name: findSpecial

methods.name: findStatic

methods.name: findStaticGetter

methods.name: findStaticSetter

methods.name: findStaticVarHandle
methods.description: Produces a VarHandle giving access to a static field name of type type declared in a class of type decl.

methods.name: findVarHandle
methods.description: Produces a VarHandle giving access to a non-static field name of type type declared in a class of type recv.

methods.name: findVirtual
methods.description: Produces a method handle for a virtual method.

methods.name: hasFullPrivilegeAccess
methods.description: Returns true if this lookup has full privilege access, i.e.

methods.name: hasPrivateAccess
methods.description: Deprecated.This method was originally designed to test PRIVATE access that implies full privilege access but MODULE access has since become independent of PRIVATE access.

methods.name: in
methods.description: Creates a lookup on the specified new lookup class.

methods.name: lookupClass
methods.description: Tells which class is performing the lookup.

methods.name: lookupModes
methods.description: Tells which access-protection classes of members this lookup object can produce.

methods.name: previousLookupClass
methods.description: Reports a lookup class in another module that this lookup object was previously teleported from, or null.

methods.name: revealDirect
methods.description: Cracks a direct method handle created by this lookup object or a similar one.

methods.name: toString
methods.description: Displays the name of the class from which lookups are to be made, followed by "/" and the name of the previous lookup class if present.

methods.name: unreflect

methods.name: unreflectConstructor

methods.name: unreflectSetter

methods.name: unreflectSpecial
methods.description: Produces a method handle for a reflected method.

methods.name: unreflectVarHandle
methods.description: Produces a VarHandle giving access to a reflected field f of type T declared in a class of type R.

constructors.name: MutableCallSite

methods.name: dynamicInvoker
methods.description: Produces a method handle equivalent to an invokedynamic instruction which has been linked to this call site.

methods.name: getTarget
methods.description: Returns the target method of the call site, which behaves like a normal field of the MutableCallSite.

methods.name: setTarget
methods.description: Updates the target method of this call site, as a normal variable.

methods.name: syncAll
methods.description: Performs a synchronization operation on each call site in the given array, forcing all other threads to throw away any cached values previously loaded from the target of any of the call sites.

methods.name: arrayConstructor
methods.description: Produces a method handle constructing arrays of a desired type, as if by the anewarray bytecode.

methods.name: arrayElementGetter
methods.description: Produces a method handle giving read access to elements of an array, as if by the aaload bytecode.

methods.name: arrayElementSetter
methods.description: Produces a method handle giving write access to elements of an array, as if by the astore bytecode.

methods.name: arrayElementVarHandle
methods.description: Produces a VarHandle giving access to elements of an array of type arrayClass.

methods.name: arrayLength
methods.description: Produces a method handle returning the length of an array, as if by the arraylength bytecode.

methods.name: byteArrayViewVarHandle
methods.description: Produces a VarHandle giving access to elements of a byte[] array viewed as if it were a different primitive array type, such as int[] or long[].

methods.name: byteBufferViewVarHandle
methods.description: Produces a VarHandle giving access to elements of a ByteBuffer viewed as if it were an array of elements of a different primitive component type to that of byte, such as int[] or long[].

methods.name: catchException

methods.name: classData
methods.description: Returns the class data associated with the lookup class of the given caller lookup object, or null.

methods.name: classDataAt
methods.description: Returns the element at the specified index in the class data, if the class data associated with the lookup class of the given caller lookup object is a List.

methods.name: collectArguments
methods.description: Adapts a target method handle by pre-processing a sub-sequence of its arguments with a filter (another method handle).

methods.name: constant
methods.description: Produces a method handle of the requested return type which returns the given constant value every time it is invoked.

methods.name: countedLoop
methods.description: Constructs a loop that runs a given number of iterations.

methods.name: countedLoop
methods.description: Constructs a loop that counts over a range of numbers.

methods.name: doWhileLoop
methods.description: Constructs a do-while loop from an initializer, a body, and a predicate.

methods.name: dropArguments
methods.description: Produces a method handle which will discard some dummy arguments before calling some other specified target method handle.

methods.name: dropArguments
methods.description: Produces a method handle which will discard some dummy arguments before calling some other specified target method handle.

methods.name: dropArgumentsToMatch
methods.description: Adapts a target method handle to match the given parameter type list.

methods.name: dropReturn
methods.description: Drop the return value of the target handle (if any).

methods.name: empty
methods.description: Produces a method handle of the requested type which ignores any arguments, does nothing, and returns a suitable default depending on the return type.

methods.name: exactInvoker
methods.description: Produces a special invoker method handle which can be used to invoke any method handle of the given type, as if by invokeExact.

methods.name: explicitCastArguments
methods.description: Produces a method handle which adapts the type of the given method handle to a new type by pairwise argument and return type conversion.

methods.name: filterArguments
methods.description: Adapts a target method handle by pre-processing one or more of its arguments, each with its own unary filter function, and then calling the target with each pre-processed argument replaced by the result of its corresponding filter function.

methods.name: filterReturnValue
methods.description: Adapts a target method handle by post-processing its return value (if any) with a filter (another method handle).

methods.name: foldArguments
methods.description: Adapts a target method handle by pre-processing some of its arguments, starting at a given position, and then calling the target with the result of the pre-processing, inserted into the original sequence of arguments just before the folded arguments.

methods.name: foldArguments
methods.description: Adapts a target method handle by pre-processing some of its arguments, and then calling the target with the result of the pre-processing, inserted into the original sequence of arguments.

methods.name: guardWithTest
methods.description: Makes a method handle which adapts a target method handle, by guarding it with a test, a boolean-valued method handle.

methods.name: identity
methods.description: Produces a method handle which returns its sole argument when invoked.

methods.name: insertArguments
methods.description: Provides a target method handle with one or more bound arguments in advance of the method handle's invocation.

methods.name: invoker
methods.description: Produces a special invoker method handle which can be used to invoke any method handle compatible with the given type, as if by invoke.

methods.name: iteratedLoop
methods.description: Constructs a loop that ranges over the values produced by an Iterator<T>.

methods.name: lookup
methods.description: Returns a lookup object with full capabilities to emulate all supported bytecode behaviors of the caller.

methods.name: loop
methods.description: Constructs a method handle representing a loop with several loop variables that are updated and checked upon each iteration.

methods.name: permuteArguments
methods.description: Produces a method handle which adapts the calling sequence of the given method handle to a new type, by reordering the arguments.

methods.name: privateLookupIn

methods.name: publicLookup

methods.name: reflectAs
methods.description: Performs an unchecked "crack" of a direct method handle.

methods.name: spreadInvoker
methods.description: Produces a method handle which will invoke any method handle of the given type, with a given number of trailing arguments replaced by a single trailing Object[] array.

methods.name: tableSwitch

methods.name: throwException

methods.name: tryFinally

fields.name: BASIC_ISO_DATE
fields.description: The ISO date formatter that formats or parses a date without an offset, such as '20111203'.

fields.name: ISO_DATE
fields.description: The ISO date formatter that formats or parses a date with the offset if available, such as '2011-12-03' or '2011-12-03+01:00'.

fields.name: ISO_DATE_TIME
fields.description: The ISO-like date-time formatter that formats or parses a date-time with the offset and zone if available, such as '2011-12-03T10:15:30', '2011-12-03T10:15:30+01:00' or '2011-12-03T10:15:30+01:00[Europe/Paris]'.

fields.name: ISO_INSTANT
fields.description: The ISO instant formatter that formats or parses an instant in UTC, such as '2011-12-03T10:15:30Z'.

fields.name: ISO_LOCAL_DATE

fields.name: ISO_LOCAL_DATE_TIME
fields.description: The ISO date-time formatter that formats or parses a date-time without an offset, such as '2011-12-03T10:15:30'.

fields.name: ISO_LOCAL_TIME
fields.description: The ISO time formatter that formats or parses a time without an offset, such as '10:15' or '10:15:30'.

fields.name: ISO_OFFSET_DATE
fields.description: The ISO date formatter that formats or parses a date with an offset, such as '2011-12-03+01:00'.

fields.name: ISO_OFFSET_DATE_TIME
fields.description: The ISO date-time formatter that formats or parses a date-time with an offset, such as '2011-12-03T10:15:30+01:00'.

fields.name: ISO_OFFSET_TIME
fields.description: The ISO time formatter that formats or parses a time with an offset, such as '10:15+01:00' or '10:15:30+01:00'.

fields.name: ISO_ORDINAL_DATE
fields.description: The ISO date formatter that formats or parses the ordinal date without an offset, such as '2012-337'.

fields.name: ISO_TIME
fields.description: The ISO time formatter that formats or parses a time, with the offset if available, such as '10:15', '10:15:30' or '10:15:30+01:00'.

fields.name: ISO_WEEK_DATE
fields.description: The ISO date formatter that formats or parses the week-based date without an offset, such as '2012-W48-6'.

fields.name: ISO_ZONED_DATE_TIME
fields.description: The ISO-like date-time formatter that formats or parses a date-time with offset and zone, such as '2011-12-03T10:15:30+01:00[Europe/Paris]'.

fields.name: RFC_1123_DATE_TIME
fields.description: The RFC-1123 date-time formatter, such as 'Tue, 3 Jun 2008 11:05:30 GMT'.

fields.name: CONCURRENT
fields.description: Characteristic value signifying that the element source may be safely concurrently modified (allowing additions, replacements, and/or removals) by multiple threads without external synchronization.

fields.name: DISTINCT
fields.description: Characteristic value signifying that, for each pair of encountered elements x, y, !x.equals(y).

fields.name: IMMUTABLE
fields.description: Characteristic value signifying that the element source cannot be structurally modified; that is, elements cannot be added, replaced, or removed, so such changes cannot occur during traversal.

fields.name: NONNULL
fields.description: Characteristic value signifying that the source guarantees that encountered elements will not be null.

fields.name: ORDERED
fields.description: Characteristic value signifying that an encounter order is defined for elements.

fields.name: SIZED
fields.description: Characteristic value signifying that the value returned from estimateSize() prior to traversal or splitting represents a finite size that, in the absence of structural source modification, represents an exact count of the number of elements that would be encountered by a complete traversal.

fields.name: SORTED
fields.description: Characteristic value signifying that encounter order follows a defined sort order.

fields.name: SUBSIZED
fields.description: Characteristic value signifying that all Spliterators resulting from trySplit() will be both SIZED and SUBSIZED.
